  "explanations": [
    {
      "text": "Use は after a noun or phrase to show the topic: what the sentence is about. It often feels like “as for…” in English, but you usually translate it naturally without those words.",
      "title": "The topic marker は"
    },
    {
      "text": "は does not give meaning like “in,” “to,” or “at.” It simply points to the thing you are going to comment on. The information after は tells us something about that topic.",
      "title": "What は does"
    }
  ],
